The '''mountain robin'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.xeno-canto.org/species/Petroica-bivittata |title=Mountain Robin · ''Petroica bivittata'' · De Vis, 1897 |work=xeno-canto |publisher= Xeno-canto Foundation |accessdate=1 March 2019}}</ref> ('''''Petroica bivittata'''''), also known as '''subalpine robin''', '''alpine robin''' or ''' cloud-forest robin''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Petroicidae]]. It is found sparsely throughout the [[New Guinea Highlands]].<ref name=IUCN/>

Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s and subalpine shrubland.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hbw.com/species/subalpine-robin-petroica-bivittata|title=Subalpine Robin (Petroica bivittata)|website=www.hbw.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>  The robin eats insects, caught in flight.<ref name=":0" />

Two subspecies have been noted, ''Petroica bivittata bivittata'' and ''Petroica bivittata caudata.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://animaldiversity.org/accounts/Petroica_bivittata/classification/|title=ADW: Petroica bivittata: CLASSIFICATION|website=animaldiversity.org|access-date=2020-03-07}}</ref>

